results.name: Real part of the multiplier m of the multiperfect Gaussian integer A100884(n)+i*A100885(n).
comment: Let the Gaussian integer z = A100884(n)+i*A100885(n). Then a(n) = Re(m) = Re( sigma(z)/z) .
